<1ST_LINE>r p AM-CVN--CorettaScottKing     08-17 0147</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-CVN--Coretta Scott King,130</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>MLK's Widow Attends GOP Convention</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW ORLEANS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Coretta Scott King attended the Republican
National Convention Tuesday night, getting a kiss from Barbara Bush
and listening raptly to New Jersey Gov. Thomas Kean's keynote
address.
   The widow of the Rev. Martin Luther King Jr. sat in the vice
president's box in the Louisiana Superdome and was one of the first
people Mrs. Bush greeted when she made her entrance.
   Mrs. King also stopped by the Georgia delegation on the floor of
the Superdome. She left after Kean spoke and before Pat Robertson
began his talk.
   Another civil rights leader, the Rev. Benjamin Hooks, the
longtime executive director of the NAACP, delivered the closing
benediction Tuesday.
   Hooks called Kean's address ``a great speech ... one of the best
speeches I've heard in the 12 conventions I've attended. I enjoyed
it very much.''
</TEXT>
