<1ST_LINE>r a AM-SovietVisit     08-17 0121</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Soviet Visit,0124</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Soviet Delegation to Visit Reagan's Boyhood Home</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DIXON, Ill. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Soviet delegation from Dickson, Siberia,
will visit its sister city of Dixon, Illinois, and stop at
President Reagan's boyhood home next week.
   Mayor James E. Dixon of the host city announced the visit
Tuesday, which he described as the ``Dixon summit.''
   The Soviet delegation will visit the house where Reagan grew up,
attend a reception at the local high school, and tour area grain
and dairy farms.
   The Soviet delegation will arrive Wednesday and leave the
following Tuesday, the mayor said.
   Problems in getting visas delayed a May visit by the Soviets,
including Dickson Mayor Nikolai T. Kartamyshev, journalist Boris S.
Ivanov and an interpreter.
</TEXT>
