   I believe we can keep America more competitive in the world if
we keep those tax cuts in place.
   And I believe if we help to get those small businesses started
and get those big businesses smarter, and if we make a national
commitment that America will not settle for second best.
   And I believe, I believe that we can keep America secure if we
keep her strong.
   You know, I also have another belief, and that is that we can
make America's neighborhoods and communities safe if we're tough
enough with the criminals instead of being tough on the law-abiding
citizens.
   Let's be a little _ (applause) _ let's rededicate ourselves to
safe neighborhoods, and to supporting those who support the laws.
   And I believe, I believe most of all that what makes America
great is values _ values like faith and freedom, values like
neighborhood and community, and above all values like family.
   And I have to confess it's my family that gives me strength, and
I don't think I'm alone in America. Families are the thread with
which this country's magic quilt is held together.
   And I brought a few friends of mine along to New Orleans today.
   And if you don't mind, I'd like to introduce them to you now.
   First, you all know the person who keeps me ticking. What you
may not know is how hard she's worked in these last eight years to
help those kids in America who don't know how to read, help them
learn to read, and that's my wife, Barbara. (Applause.)
   And that's what she's done all her life _ all her life, help
other people make the best of themselves.
   Ladies and gentlemen, the secret weapon of the Bush campaign is
my wife, Barbara, and the other secret weapons are my five children
_ I should say ``ours'' _ our five children and our 10
grandchildren, and our children's spouses.
   I'd like to introduce all of them to you here today.
</TEXT>
