<2ND_LINE>PM-Weatherpage Weather,0418</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Thunderstorms Hit North And Central States As Heat Continues</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
   Thunderstorms ripped across parts of Michigan, Minnesota, the
Dakotas, Nebraska and Colorado early today while heat continued to
grip the Midwest.
   Early morning temperatures of 86 degrees were registered in
Minneapolis and St. Louis after winds gusted up to 83 mph at Grand
Marais in northern Minnesota on the Canadian border.
   Tornadoes touched down Tuesday evening in northern North Dakota
near Minot. There were no reports of injuries. Hail the size of
golf balls hit Willow City, N.D., and hail up to three inches in
diameter fell at Lakota, N.D.
   Three-quarter inch hail fell at Salvo, N.C., and hail up to an
inch in diameter hit Conetoe, N.C.
   Wind damage from evening thunderstorms occurred south of Dallas
in Ferris and Maypearl and in Michigan's Upper Peninsula near
Houghton.
   Thunderstorms in the South and West hit parts of New Mexico,
Arkansas, Louisiana and Mississippi early today, and rainshowers
dampened western Washington state.
   Today's forecast called for showers and thunderstorms across the
central Gulf of Mexico, central and coastal Florida, New England,
the Great Lakes and southern Minnesota.
   High temperatures were forecast to be in the 80s or 90s across
much of the nation; the 70s along the Pacific Coast, the middle 90s
to near 105 degrees from the mid-Atlantic states through the lower
Ohio Valley, the middle Mississippi Valley and lower Missouri
Valley into the central Plains; and about 115 degrees over the
desert Southwest.
   Temperatures around the nation at 3 a.m. EDT ranged from 43
degrees at Yellowstone, Mont., to 94 degrees at Phoenix, Ariz.
   Other reports:
   _East: Atlanta 76 fair; Boston 67 partly cloudy; Buffalo 73
cloudy; Charleston, S.C. 74 fair; Cincinnati 73 fair; Cleveland 73
partly cloudy; Detroit 79 fair; Miami 78 showery; New York 76 fair;
Philadelphia 72 fair; Pittsburgh 72 cloudy; Portland, Maine 64
fair; Washington 76 fair.
   _Central: Bismarck 71 fair; Chicago 83 fair; Dallas-Fort Worth
85 fair; Denver 62 partly cloudy; Des Moines 81 fair; Indianapolis
80 fair; Kansas City 83 fair; Minneapolis-St. Paul 86 fair;
Nashville 82 fair; New Orleans 78 fair; St. Louis 86 fair.
   _West: Albuquerque 65 fair; Anchorage 62 windy; Las Vegas 80
fair; Los Angeles 63 partly cloudy; Phoenix 94 fair; Salt Lake City
66 fair; San Diego 66 partly cloudy; San Francisco 58 fair; Seattle
59 cloudy.
   _Canada: Montreal 64 partly cloudy; Toronto 70 cloudy.
</TEXT>
