<HEAD>Pakistani Leader, U.S. Ambassador Involved In Crash, Diplomats Say</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ISLAMABAD, Pakistan (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An aircraft carrying President
Mohammad Zia ul-Haq and U.S. Ambassador Arnold Raphel crashed
Wednesday after taking off from an airport in Lahore, U.S.
diplomatis said.
   The diplomats, who spoke on condition of anonymity, said they
did not know if there were any survivors. Lahore is 180 miles
southeast of Islamabad.
   In Washington, congressional and Reagan administration sources
confirmed that Raphel was on board the aircraft. The sources, who
spoke on condition of anonymity, had no further details on the
crash.
