<HEAD>Woman Shoots Two Police Officers with One of Their Guns</HEAD>
<DATELINE>GRAND RAPIDS, Mich. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A woman arrested for creating a
disturbance wrestled a gun from a police officer, shooting him and
a sheriff's deputy before she was restrained, police said.
   Kent County Sheriff's Deputy Jack Hertel, 34, was hospitalized
in fair condition today with a wound to the stomach. Grand Rapids
Police Officer Richard Schaafsma was treated and released after a
shot grazed his head.
   The shootings occurred just before midnight Tuesday when the
30-year-old woman, whose name was withheld pending arraignment,
grabbed the gun from Schaafsma's holster while she was being
transported to the Kent County Jail from the jail's garage,
Undersheriff James Dougan said.
   The woman shot Schaafsma once before turning the weapon on
Hertel, an unarmed corrections officer, Undersheriff James Dougan
said. She emptied the .38-caliber gun, firing six times, he said.
