<1ST_LINE>r a PM-BodyFound     08-17 0252</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>PM-Body Found,0259</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Police: For 10 Days, Youths Hid Friend's Body After Shotgun
Slaying</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. PETERSBURG, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Three brothers playing with a
shotgun panicked after it accidentally discharged, killing a fourth
boy, and dragged their friend's body to a vacant home where it
remained for 10 days, police said.
   ``The kids got panicky. They thought he was dead and they took
him over to the apartment next door,'' said police Detective Ralph
Pflieger.
   An autopsy was scheduled for today to determine whether the
14-year-old died instantly, Pflieger said. The youth's name was
withheld pending positive identification through dental records.
   The teen-ager's mother reported him missing Aug. 8, and police
found the decomposed body in a vacant house on Tuesday.
   The names of the three brothers, ages 12, 14 and 15, were not
released because they are juveniles. No charges have been filed, a
police spokeswoman said.
   A 14-year-old brother who came forward told authorities they
were playing 10 days earlier at an apartment occupied by a cousin
of the brothers, Pflieger said. The cousin wasn't home when the the
foursome found a shotgun and began fooling around with it, police
said. The weapon discharged and struck the other 14-year-old, the
youth told police.
   The three brothers dragged their friend's body next door and
left him there, Pflieger said.
   The 14-year-old told an adult about the shooting after he was
taken into custody at Pinellas County Juvenile Detention Center
later on a charge related to an auto theft, officials said.
</TEXT>
