<1ST_LINE>r a AM-BRF--BestCities-Women     08-17 0178</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-BRF--Best Cities-Women,0182</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Go West, Young Woman</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Looking for a nice place to live? Go west, young
woman _ way west.
   Seattle is the No. 1 most liveable spot for women in the United
States, according to research conducted by two urban studies
specialists for Savvy magazine. The results appear in its September
issue.
   Seattle came in with 23 of a possible 30 points in the study,
which considered factors such as cost of living, violent crime,
professional opportunities, number of physicians and city spending
for education.
   Those who don't want to go west can always go east. Ranking
second with 22 points was Boston; tied for third were Pittsburgh
and Washington at 21.
   Ranking fourth _ and supporting what Mary Richards has known for
years _ was Minneapolis-St. Paul (20), while San Francisco (19)
came in fifth. Rounding out the rankings, in order, were Chicago
(17), Houston (16), Los Angeles (15), New York (14) and Atlanta
(13).
   ``Atlantans may scream, and New Yorkers may sneer, but numbers
don't lie,'' the magazine concluded.
</TEXT>
