<HEAD>NEW ORLEANS: on trying.</HEAD>
<TEXT>
   Q. Senator Quayle, you have backed Senator Domenici's budget
proposal that calls for $22 billion in tax increases. Are you going
to be at odds with the platform of the Republicans that calls for
no tax increases?
   Quayle: Absolutely not, because, let's face it, we have economic
growth today because of the Reagan-Bush tax cuts.
   And the vice president has pledged, and I support him in that
pledge, that we are simply not going to raise taxes.
   It would be foolhardy.
   Why would we want to raise taxes and try to send this economy
into a downturn?
   We have gotten economic growth through tax cuts.
   Q. Why did you support a budget that called for a tax increase
in fiscal year '83 of $22 billion?
