be doing a little of that in my speech tomorrow, and both the
senator and I will be doing a lot of that in the campaign.
   And if we can spell it out, if we can compel him to be as
specific as I have been, and as both of us will be, then I think we
will have made real headway.
   You don't have to resort to name-calling, out of the Democratic
convention, or out of the Republican convention.
   Susan?
