<1ST_LINE>r p AM-CVN--GOP-Abortion     08-17 0307</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-CVN--GOP-Abortion,310</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Right to Life Group Praises GOP Ticket</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW ORLEANS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The head of the National Right to Life
Committee praised the Republican ticket Wednesday and accused
Democratic nominee Michael Dukakis of being ``a pro-abortion
zealot.''
   Dr. J.C. Willke, the group's president, hailed Sen. Dan Quayle
of Indiana as ``a consistent supporter of the civil rights of all
Americans, including those in the womb.''
   ``There has never been a clearer choice for president than the
one between George Bush ... and Michael Dukakis, who supports
unrestricted legal abortion and government funding of abortion,''
he said at a news conference.
   He called the Democratic ticket of Dukakis and Sen. Lloyd
Bentsen of Texas ``the most pro-abortion ticket of the century.''
   He said Bentsen has voted often in favor of federal funding of
abortion and only once against it in the past 10 years.
   Bentsen says he favors Medicaid funding of abortion only in
cases or rape or incest or to save the mother's life.
   Dukakis has said he personally opposes abortion but believes
women should have the right to decide.
   Willke said that as a Massachusetts state legislator in 1970,
Dukakis introduced a bill to legalize abortion on demand, and later
as governor he vetoed bills containing abortion-funding
restrictions.
   Dukakis is not only pro-choice, ``he is a pro-abortion zealot,''
Willke charged.
   Bush favors a Constitutional amendment to ban abortion, except
in cases of rape or incest or to save the mother's life. He favor's
Medicaid funding only to save the mother's life.
   The Democrats' platform states, ``the right of reproductive
choice should be guaranteed regardless of ability to pay.'' It does
not use the word ``abortion.''
   The GOP platform contains several planks decrying abortion and
committing the party to work against it, including appointment of
judges who ``respect ... the sanctity of innocent human life.''
</TEXT>
