<1ST_LINE>r a AM-MurphreeSentence     08-17 0308</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>AM-Murphree Sentence,0304</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Woman In Swaggart Case Sentenced To Six Months For Prostitution</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By LINDA ASHTON</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>GRETNA, La. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Debra Murphree, who says she posed nude for
evangelist Jimmy Swaggart, was sentenced Wednesday to six months in
jail in an unrelated prostitution case.
   Miss Murphree, 28, was arrested Sept. 21, 1987, at a motel in
suburban New Orleans. She pleaded guilty to a misdemeanor charge of
prostitution May 20, three months after she identified herself as
the woman at the center of the Swaggart scandal.
   Swaggart never acknowledged any encounter with Miss Murphree,
but tearfully confessed from the pulpit that he had committed
unspecified sins.
   District Judge Wallace LeBrun said that under the state's
multiple offender law, he was compelled to sentence Miss Murphree
to jail because of three prior convictions in prostitution cases.
   Miss Murphree, who did not speak during the brief hearing, was
put in the custody of deputies immediately to be jailed.
   ``Obviously she committed the crime,'' said defense attorney Tom
Weymann. ``But it's a shock, given the circumstances.'' He said he
would appeal.
   Weymann said Miss Murphree had begun to turn her life around
since the Swaggart incident became public. She had returned to her
hometown of Patoka, Ind., where she was living with her parents and
three children, ages 7, 8, and 10.
   She was making arrangements to return to school to study
interior design, her lawyer said.
   The incident rocked Swaggart's $140 million a year evangelical
empire and cost him his credentials as a minister of the Assemblies
of God when he refused to stop preaching for a year.
   Miss Murphree sold her story about the Swaggart encounter to
Penthouse magazine, accompanied by a series of explicit black and
white photos showing the poses and things she said Swaggart asked
her to do in the motel room.
</TEXT>
