<2ND_LINE>AM-Obit-Mathsson,0105</2ND_LINE>
<HEAD>Designer of Scandinavia Furniture Dead, 81</HEAD>
<DATELINE>STOCKHOLM, Sweden (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Bruno Mathsson, a fifth-generation
carpenter who gained international fame as a creator of
Scandinavian-design furniture, died Wednesday, it was reported. He
was 81.
   The designer died at his home in Varnamo, 210 miles south of
Stockholm, the national news agency TT reported. It said nothing of
the cause of death and funeral arrangements.
   Mathsson, breaking with traditional carved wood designs,
introduced functional chairs in the 1930s with burlap seats to fit
the body's shape.
   He became a teacher to generations of Swedes, establishing a
fund to sponsor young designers.
</TEXT>
