<1ST_LINE>u p BC-CVN--GrammTextExcerpts     08-17 0521</1ST_LINE>
<2ND_LINE>BC-CVN--Gramm Text Excerpts,500</2ND_LINE>
<DATELINE>NEW ORLEANS (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Here are excerpts from the prepared text of
the speech by Sen. Phil Gramm of Texas nominating Vice President
George Bush for president at the Republican National Convention
Wednesday night.
   ... Do you remember what the world was like in January of 1981
when Ronald Reagan and George Bush took the oath of office?
   The amnesia merchants of the Atlanta convention want us to
forget that when the Democrats left the White House, inflation and
interest rates were at the highest levels in American history. ...
   Given his record, is there anybody here who doubts that a
President Dukakis would raise our taxes?
   Is there anybody here who doubts that a President Dukakis would
spend our workers into poverty? Is there anybody here who doubts
that a President Dukakis would cut defense, and wimp America and
endanger peace?
   Is there anybody here who doubts that a President Dukakis would
expand the power of government and its control over our businesses,
our families, our churches, and our lives. ...
   We will never have to worry about George Bush's willingness to
stand up for America.
   He knows from real life experience that peace comes through
strength, not through wishful thinking. ...
   ... George Bush was the youngest pilot in the Navy. ... On a
bombing run at Chichi Jima, his plane was hit and both of his
crewmen were killed. As flames swept over the wings and cockpit,
George Bush remembered the first obligation of a leader is to
accomplish the mission.
   He stayed on his bombing run and dropped two tons of TNT on the
target. He then turned his crippled plane out to sea and bailed
out. ... With blood streaming down his face and a .38 revolver in
one hand, he paddled away from the shore with the other hand to be
rescued by a submarine.
   Let me read from his citation for the Distinguished Flying Cross.
   ``By his superb airmanship, courageous actions, and loyal
dedication to duty, Lieutenant Bush reflected great credit upon
himself and upheld the highest traditions of the United States
Naval Service,'' signed, Franklin Delano Roosevelt.
   My friends, when Michael Dukakis vetoed that bill providing for
the Pledge of Allegiance to the American flag in Massachusetts in
public schools he was not representing the views of George Bush. ...
   ... George Bush is the greatest vice president this nation has
ever had. He has always made us proud.
   When the Soviet Union targeted a new class of nuclear weapons at
Western Europe, destroying the military balance and threatening
peace, Vice President Bush flew to Europe to meet with our NATO
allies. ...
   As chairman of the South Florida Task Force, George Bush put
together the nation's first really successful effort to protect our
children from illegal drugs. ... George Bush knows that the only
way you can deal with drug pushers is to grab them by the throat.
...
   ... With George Bush as our president, building on the success
of the last eight years, there is no limit to the future of the
American people. ...
</TEXT>
