<TEXT>
   A Greek immigrant, saying thanks yet
again for the U.S. relief packages he received as a child, threw a
picnic for thousands of senior citizens Wednesday.
   ``This country's got a heart so big,'' said restaurateur Lou
Pappan, who handed out silver dollars to the guests at his 14th
summer picnic. ``Of all the countries I could have went to, here I
am. I came to the United States, the best country in the world.''
   The 12-hour picnic, a country hoedown in Bradys Run Park, has
become a summertime tradition for senior citizens in Beaver County,
a depressed patch of steel country about 25 miles west of
Pittsburgh.
</TEXT>
