<HEAD>Montgomery Ward Agrees to End Claims</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The Federal Trade Commission says Montgomery
Ward has promised to stop making claims about home appliances that
the government charges were false.
   The commission said in an annoucement Tuesday that the giant
retailer has signed a consent agreement to stop making reliability
claims for products unless it has evidence to support them and to
stop making contested claims relating to maintenance of products.
